  "explanation": "The SSH check uses paramiko.SSHClient.connect with a required username and either password or private key, then verifies transport.is_authenticated(). Without credentials the check cannot exercise its core service check (ssh.can_connect) nor the SFTP probe, so auto-config cannot meaningfully enable it. Detecting an SSH server on port 22 is trivial, but it is also out-of-scope - the integration is designed to validate authenticated access for a specific user.",
